# SOTA Validation

**Canonical source:** `.sanctuary/methodologies/sota-validation.md`

Read the canonical file for the full methodology (graduation table, branch protocol, Railway setup, anti-patterns, documented exceptions). Summary below as fallback.

## Summary — Risk Graduation

| Change | Risk | Flow |
|---|---|---|
| Surgical bug fix | Low | Branch → commit → merge to main |
| LLM behavior change (prompt, voice, formatters) | Medium | SOTA branch → 3-5 days observation with Oscar → merge if net positive |
| Structural (schema, migrations, queues, payments, auth) | High | Parallel Railway service + secondary WhatsApp number + cloned DB → 5-7 days |
| New SOTA coder model | High | Full methodology, dedicated branch (`<model>-adventures`) |
| New SOTA product model | Critical | Parallel service + secondary number + 7-10 days + cross-model debug any regression |

**Promotion criteria:** No regression + Net positive + Human validation (Oscar or founder). 3/3 → merge. 1-2/3 → cherry-pick. 0/3 → archive.

**When in doubt, escalate one level.**
